                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>London</placeName>\n                                        <date>19th Adar 5611</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <date>21st Feby 1851</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>Revd and Dear Sir,</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(3)\">In compliance with your request and indeed<lb/> I\n                                        consider it no more than a duty on my part towards you to\n                                        acquaint<lb/> you that on <date>Monday</date> afternoon last\n                                        I received yr. Packet a letter from <persName>Mr.\n                                                  H.</persName><lb/>\n                                        <date>Feby 5th</date>: I have very little time left on my\n                                        hands now, I must most fervently pray<lb/> and entreat you\n                                        to excuse haste and writing, as I have been so very<lb/>\n                                        busy this day; in other duties and replying to <persName>Mr.\n                                                  H.</persName> that it is approaching to\n                                                  <add>שבת</add><lb/> but I will give you some\n                                        little extracts of his letter for <hi rend=\"underline\">your\n                                                  guidance</hi> Trusting<lb/> to your honor and\n                                        integrity that you will not make use of my name neither<lb/>\n                                        in this case, or in the other of <persName>M.</persName> for\n                                        heaven be my witness that there is no harm<add>?</add><lb/>\n                                        but <sic>dont</sic> wish my name in question since we have\n                                        all <hi rend=\"underline\">some good friends</hi> always<lb/>\n                                        on the <hi rend=\"underline\">look out</hi>. therefore my Dr.\n                                        friend let it be <add>סוד ה' ליראיו</add> the information is\n                                        for<lb/> your guidance at the same time I assure you from\n                                        the 1st syllable to the last<lb/> there is not one\n                                        disrespectful to you, on the contrary he speaks\n                                        high—where<lb/> I said to him in my letter <del>he\n                                                  replies</del>\n                                        <hi rend=\"underline\">that none should be revered unless\n                                                  for</hi><lb/> high moral &amp; religious\n                                        diligency\" \"<hi rend=\"underline\">a man in holy office should\n                                                  be raised &amp;</hi><lb/>\n                                        <hi rend=\"underline\">not lowered</hi>—he replies, \"no\n                                        removal has taken place—that nothing has been<lb/> done to\n                                        lower our former Hazan in the estimation of the world\n                                        indeed—and<lb/> so <persName>Mr. H</persName> goes on\n                                        replying on my remarks—<sic>than</sic> he goes on informing\n                                        me<lb/> I may say, almost the same as you did in your first\n                                        letter. I will go on now with fewer traits<lb/> \"In the\n                                        first place not a person in the whole congregation says or\n                                        can<lb/> say aught against <persName>Mr. Leeser's</persName>\n                                        reputation.\"—I flattered myself<lb/> that I was and that\n                                                  <persName>Mr Leeser</persName> also considered me\n                                        his friend—</p>\n                              <p>I feel satisfied that the congregation will not again find a\n                                        person<lb/> combining all the qualities of a Hazan and\n                                        lecturer and possessing<lb/> the talents of <persName>Mr.\n                                                  Leeser</persName> and no one desires or can\n                                        detract from his<lb/> merits he has done more for the Jews\n                                        in <placeName>America</placeName> than any other</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3t43jp2h/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
