                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3t43jp2h/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>know if you have seen <persName>Mr. H.</persName> I must confess\n                                        that his letter is of a <add>?</add><lb/> and that his\n                                        feelings are respectful towards you. Wishing you every\n                                        success</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(7)\">I remain</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(7)\">yours most truly</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(8)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">D Meldola</persName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>I must add that I wrote to <persName>Mr. H.</persName> that as<lb/>\n                                                  \"<hi rend=\"underline\">since my first reading your\n                                                  works I entertaind</hi><lb/>\n                                        <hi rend=\"underline\">the highest respect for your name\" the\n                                                  greatest esteem\".</hi> I believe I did my duty\n                                        towards<lb/> you as much as a father, now you must do the\n                                        same towards me as a son take<lb/> my advice <sic>dont</sic>\n                                        be too hard get <persName>Mr. H.</persName> your friend\n                                        again, give in a little, and <sic>dont</sic><lb/> allow your\n                                        opponents to have their way, I wish I was there to impress\n                                        all this on your<lb/> mind for it is only <add>אורייתא הוא\n                                                  דקא מרתחא כך</add> abandon this for a while\n                                                  <add>וחזקת והיית לאיש וכל אשר אתה עושה ה' מצליח\n                                                  אכת\"ו</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>Hebrew</add></p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3t43jp2h/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
